    "html": "<section class=\"catalog-card-content\"><div class=\"problem-body\">\n<p>While designing his video game, Elliott decided to replace some of his long sentences describing hops with symbols. For example, to represent where the frog traveled and landed in part (a) of problem 3-90, he wrote:</p>\n<p class=\"mathline\">$3 + 4 - 7 + 6$</p>\n<ol type=\"a\">\n<li>How does Elliott's expression represent the words in part (a) of problem 3-90? Where did the $3$ come from? Why is one number subtracted?</li>\n<li>If another set of hops was represented by $5 - 10 + 2 + 1$, describe the frog's movements. Where did the frog start and where did it end up?</li>\n<li>One game used the expression $-5 + 10$. Where does the frog start? Where does it end up? What is special about the ending point?</li>\n<li>Another game had a frog start at the opposite of $-3$, hop $5$ units to the left, $9$ units to the right, and then hop to its opposite position. Write an expression to represent the frog's motion on the number line. Where did the frog end up?</li>\n<li>Where does the frog start in the expression $-(-2) + 6$? Where does it land?</li>\n</ol>\n</div></section>",
