    "html": "<section class=\"catalog-card-content\"><div class=\"problem-body\">\n<p><strong>Opposites</strong></p>\n<p>The opposite of a number is the same number but with the opposite sign $(+$ or $-)$. A number and its opposite are both the same distance from $0$ on the number line.</p>\n<p>For example, the opposite of $4$ (or $+4$) is $-4$, and the opposite of $-9$ is $-(-9)=9$ (or $+9$). The opposite of $0.5$ (or $+0.5$) is $-0.5$.</p>\n<p>The opposite of an opposite is the original number.</p>\n<p>Examples: the opposite of the opposite of $5$ is $-(-(5))$, or $5$. The opposite of the opposite of $-3$ is $-(-(-3))$, or $-3$. The opposite of zero is zero.</p>\n</div></section>",
